{
  "texts": [
    "Of those, 839 (61.6%) tweet more in UA after the war, with 566 (41.5%) reporting a significant behavioural change (z > 1.96, p < 0.05).",
    "Out of those 850 users, 341 (25%) even switch to predominately tweeting in UA (>80% of tweets), i.e.",
    "perform a hard-switch, with 296 (21.7%) statistically significant hardswitches (z > 1.96, p < 0.05).",
    "We pick those 296 users and plot their weekly language proportion over time in Fig. 6.",
    "Red points denote 100% of the tweets being phrased in RU, blue points denote the same in UA."
  ]
}